# Editing config.go

`config.go` is the single source of truth for all tunable parameters.

## Adding a New Repo

Add to the `githubRepos` slice. The format is `"owner/repo"`.

## Modifying AI Prompts

- `systemPrompt` + `userPromptTmpl` — concise Telegram summary (Chinese)
- `deepSystemPromptZH` + `deepUserPromptTmplZH` — deep analysis (Chinese)
- `deepSystemPromptEN` + `deepUserPromptTmplEN` — deep analysis (English)

When modifying prompts:
- Keep ZH and EN versions structurally aligned
- Prompt templates use `%s` verbs via `fmt.Sprintf` — do not break the verb order
- Test changes by running locally with a known release before pushing

## Constants

| Constant | Purpose |
|----------|---------|
| `telegramMsgLimit` | Max rune length for Telegram messages (4000) |
| `releasesPerPage` | GitHub API per_page for releases (5) |
| `versionFile` | Path to version state file |
| `pagesBranch` | Target branch for GitHub Pages |
